post_text:
La Transferencia Electrónica de Beneficios por Pandemia (P-EBT, por sus siglas en inglés) es un beneficio de alimentos único para las familias que perdieron el acceso a comidas gratuitas o a precio reducido debido al cierre de las escuelas. A fin de mayo, las escuelas les enviarán instrucciones para realizar una solicitud a las familias elegibles para la P-EBT. La solicitud de la P-EBT estará disponible la primera semana de junio.
Los beneficios de alimentos de la P-EBT son para los niños que recibieron beneficios de alimentos del Programa Asistencial de Nutrición Suplementaria (SNAP, por sus siglas en inglés) para marzo de 2020 y para los niños que estén certificados para recibir comidas gratuitas o a precio reducido en Texas durante el año escolar 2019-20. Para obtener más información, visite: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

post_text:
Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures.Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.

P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAPfood benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

May 22 at 9:25 AM ·

We are so excited! Thanks to diligent planning and a sincere desire to make this moment a true reflection of what our Tigers deserve, we will honor our Class of 2020 this evening. Many thought this event might not happen. We would like to thank the intense efforts of Dr. Bryan Hallmark, Mrs. Megan Oliver and Mrs. Laura Osborne for making this ceremony a reality for our seniors and their families. There are also many other behind the scene members of the Sealy ISD family who have dedicated much time and effort, all to give these students this opportunity. Today we can all be proud to be SEALY TIGERS!

post_text:
Sealy ISD families, staff and students,

As per Governor Abbott’s executive order issued today, Sealy ISD will remain physically closed through the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year. Instruction will continue utilizing our current digital learning platform. Sealy ISD will continue to work together to assure that we are offering the best available learning opportunities for all students through the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year.

Texas Superintendents expect additional guidance from the Commissioner of Education regarding many of the questions that remain unanswered. We will meet with the leadership team next week and forward communications to the community as decisions are made surrounding all the different questions that we have received. Thank you for partnering with us as we work to continue to support our students, families and community.
text:
Sealy ISD families, staff and students,

As per Governor Abbott’s executive order issued today, Sealy ISD will remain physically closed through the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year. Instruction will continue utilizing our current digital learning platform. Sealy ISD will continue to work together to assure that we are offering the best available learning opportunities for all students through the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year.

Texas Superintendents expect additional guidance from the Commissioner of Education regarding many of the questions that remain unanswered. We will meet with the leadership team next week and forward communications to the community as decisions are made surrounding all the different questions that we have received. Thank you for partnering with us as we work to continue to support our students, families and community.

Common symptoms of #COVID19 are fever, dry cough, & shortness of breath. If you have mild symptoms, call your doctor & #StayHome. If you develop serious symptoms, such as trouble breathing, pressure in the chest, or bluish lips or face, call your doctor & seek care immediately.

Before social distancing, each person with #COVID19 spread the virus to 2.5 more people. At that pace, most would get it, and many more people would die. But we can slow the spread. That’s why we all #StayHome. #ApartTogether we slow coronavirus.

Antes del distanciamiento social, cada persona con #COVID19 transmitió el virus a 2.5 personas.A ese ritmo, muchas personas se contagiarían, y muchas personas morirían.Pero podemos retrasar la propagación.Por eso todos quedemonos en casa y paremos el Coronavirus.#ApartTogether

post_text:
Practice Social Distancing

To avoid the spread of COVID-19 in our community, practice social distancing:
⦁ Avoid going out in public
⦁ When in public, keep six feet of distance between you and others
⦁ Follow guidance provided by local and state officials.
Get more information at https://texas.gov/covid19
#covid19 #texasstrong #stayhome



Practica el distanciamiento social

Para prevenir la propagación de COVID-19 en nuestra comunidad, practique el distanciamiento social:
• Evite salir en público
• Cuando esté en público, mantenga una distancia de seis pies entre usted y los demás.
• Seguir las recomendaciones de los funcionarios locales y estatales.
Obtenga más información en https://texas.gov/covid19
# covid19 #texasfuerte #quedateencasa

March 12th, 2020
4:45 PM Update

Sealy ISD: Due to the ever-changing situation regarding COVID-19 and in the best interest of the health, safety, and well-being of its students, staff, community, and the citizens at large, Sealy ISD will be closed next week, March 16th-20th. Employees will receive further instructions from their supervisors. Updates will continue to be shared via the District’s mass communication system, social media sites, and website.

TIGER PRIDE PROPS from Sealy Elementary!

A parent's nomination reads, "I would like to nominate Mrs. Shupak. She is my daughters secondary teacher in 3rd grade, and my daughter learns so much from her. She not only gives her all during school hours, but even after. I’ve seen her quite a few times with her daughter in tow and still being dedicated to her after school duties with her students. She is a great asset to Sealy elementary and I’m so glad my daughter has her."

Thank you Mrs. Shupak for devoting so much of yourself to our students! Sealy ISD is very fortunate that we have so many wonderful teachers that support these kids both in the classroom and in the community!

post_text:
TIGER PRIDE PROPS from SJH!

A parent wrote, "I’d like to give a shout out to SJH Band Director, Sterling Burton!

Due to a hectic schedule, I’ve never had the fortune of attending a UIL band competition until today. While I was impressed with the concert, the sight reading was a thing of beauty. Mr. Burton’s ability to coach his band speedily and with finesse shows not only his passion for music but exceptional teaching skills. I was on the edge of my seat.

Mr. Burton has converted this die-hard sports mom to a die-hard band mom. THANK YOU!"

Sealy ISD could not be more appreciative for Mr. Burton sharing his passion with our students! He is an inspiration to so many students and exhibits amazing dedication to each of them!

TIGER PRIDE PROPS from SHS.

A parent wrote, "I would like to nominate SHS Principal Megan Oliver. Mrs. Oliver is always going above and beyond for her students. She knows them individually, greets them daily in the hallway, helps them when they stumble and shows them love through compassion. She is also there to redirect them when necessary, pressing them to pursue a future, and fail or succeed, she is their biggest cheerleader! As a parent, I could not be more thankful for her commitment to this district, her campus and our kids! This woman is truly amazing!"

Sealy ISD is very grateful to the dedication Mrs. Oliver shows to her campus and her kids! We appreciate her leadership and influence!

post_text:
This weekend we had several students from Sealy Elementary and Maggie B. compete at the Southeast 6 Regional Destination Imagination Tournament. The students and parents worked very hard in the last couple of months to plan for this tournament. We are proud of the success that they had and also proud of the growth the students showed in going through this process while competing at a high level at the tournament.

Team "Super Squad"- 4th Place (Improv)
R. Reichardt, S. Eschenburg, J. Forrester, C. Gilbert, & W. Cryan
Team Manager: Carla Reichardt

Team "Idaho"- 6th Place (Scientific)
E. Avalos, M. Mendez, J. Kalinec, T. Soriano, & K. Carruthers
Team Manager: Diana D. Hoyos

Team "Sour Patch Kids- Participants (Technical)
L. Necker, P. Todd
Team Manager: Lynsie Necker
They will be donating the "Cozy Calm" they made to MBS

Congratulations to all the participants and volunteers!

post_text: We would like to thank Texas A&M Agrilife Extension for bringing the "Watch UR Bac" program to Sealy ISD. This was an amazing opportunity for the school and the community to become more aware of trends in alcohol and substance abuse. We appreciate all the parents and community members who came to learn about these dangerous trends facing our youth. Together we can help keep our kids safe!

post_text:
TIGER PRIDE PROPS from MBS!

A parent wrote, "Early in the fall we noticed that our daughter was having issues with certain subjects. I casually talked to Mrs. Majarevich about it at a church event and the next week she pulled our daughter out of class to see if she could offer any insight. She has a full schedule of students she helps and did not have to spend this time with our student, but she did because she truly cares. This meeting helped us make the decision to look into our daughter’s challenges further and she’ll be getting the support she needs. Thank you to Mrs. Majarevich for your care and love!"

Congratulations Mrs. Majarevich! You are a tremendous asset to all students at Sealy ISD!

A parent wrote, "I would like to recognize Coach Jenkins from SJH. Getting a new coach is never easy on a child. However Coach came in and has done a tremendous job in the two seasons of sports already. He does not look down on an athlete for a mistake but instead helps them learn from it. He shows so much compassion for his athletes that even when they are not in school he keeps up with them. Sealy Junior High is definitely lucky to have a great coach to help these athletes get ready for high school. Thanks coach for all your hard work and dedication to our children."

Thank you Coach Jenkins for your commitment to these Tigers!

TIGER PRIDE PROPS from MBS for Ms. Sodolak.

A parent emailed, "My student has always struggled in math. At my parent conference, I asked her if she felt I should seek help from a tutor like I did the year before. She asked me to wait. She wanted more time to work with him on her own. And she did it! His grade increased and it isn't a struggle to get him to do his homework anymore because he understands and that is because of Ms. Sodolak! He even made the A/B Honor Roll. His confidence has increased because of her help. Thank you Ms. Sodolak!"

Thank you Ms. Sodolak for your sincere dedication to all of our students!

post_text:
TIGER PRIDE PROPS from SJH.

A parent of two junior high students wrote, "I would like to give a Tiger Props shoutout to SJHS principal, Dr. Laura Villaflor. Dr. Villaflor has provided a wide range of topics in her weekly Smore newsletters including the dangers of vaping, viral challenges, and other subject matter pertinent to our middle school aged kids. These discussion are needed and very much appreciated!

She also called upon parents to become more involved and has succeeded in doing so. She, along with the help of parents, implemented the WatchDOGS program and is working on organizing a first ever PTA for the school.

Thank you, Dr. Villaflor, for involving parents more and making sure our voices are heard!"

His accomplishments with our children have been numerous but pale in comparison to the impact he has made on the students and community of Sealy. He is always willing to give of his time and knowledge to those seeking to learn and grow. "

Sealy ISD is very fortunate that Mr. Oliver has made this district his home. Thank you for your commitment to our students and for all your hard work promoting trade skills and agricultural education!

TIGER PRIDE PROPS from Sealy High School.

A parent wrote, "I want to thank Ms. Jane Hoskins for going above and beyond to help my child understand her class. Last night my student reported that Ms. Hoskins is a great math teacher. TIGER PRIDE PROPS from SJH & SHS. A parent wrote...

"I would like to nominate Coach Montgomery. His powerful, positive influence on the students is truly remarkable. However, last Thursday at the Freshman football game, I witnessed him in a true act of love and care. It was freezing cold with a strong north wind blowing. A student who had just finished playing his game was working the chains for the next game. The student only had his football jersey on with no long sleeves or jacket. Coach Montgomery saw that the student was shaking from the cold and he removed his jacket and gave it to the student to wear. Coach Montgomery not only "talks the talk, but he also walks the walk." What a wonderful example he sets for all of us. Sealy ISD and this community is blessed to have Coach Montgomery."

We couldn't agree more! He is a very positive role model and influence on all of our staff and students. Sealy ISD is a better place because of Coach Montgomery.

SHS Student Council & NHS are asking for community support for their local Wreaths Across America ceremony.

REMEMBER the Fallen. . . HONOR those who Serve. . . TEACH our children the value of Freedom.

On Saturday, December 14, 2019 at 8:30 AM, Wreaths Across America will be at Sealy Cemetery to Remember and Honor our veterans through the laying of Remembrance wreaths on the graves of our country's fallen heroes and the act of saying the name of each and every veteran aloud.

Please help our location lay wreaths at as many graves as possible by clicking the link below. Or, if you would like to volunteer to participate in the wreath laying ceremony, please click the “Volunteer” button next to the cemetery name, and don't forget to click the "Invite" button to invite your friends and family to join you.

Thank you so much for supporting Sealy Cemetery and Wreaths Across America!

Sealy FFA and Jr FFA just wrapped up another successful Austin Co Fair. Over 200 entries and 90 FFA and Jr FFA members competed in events, contests and exhibiting livestock. The list of results is impressive and indicates the hard work by many. 68 Tigers earned a spot in the premium auction earning over $260,000 before add ons.
Multiple high placing, champion buckles and most importantly lessons learned and lives impacted through experience from start to finish.
Congratulations to these Sealy FFA members and a huge thanks for supporting our members. We are still working to compile the impressive list of the full results. Once we get those, we will share.

post_text: Sealy ISD welcomed back faculty and staff for the 2019-2020 school year. Convocation began with a spirit contest between the campuses. Following the cheers, Mr. Kinney from the RAP Program and Sealy ISD School Board President Ryan Reichardt both gave amazing speeches. The amount of community support for the district and the students was evidenced in their words. Sealy ISD Assistant Superintendent, Dr. Chris Summers then closed out the session with a keynote address. We are very excited to be back and can not wait to work to have the best year for our kids!

post_text: Ms. Magjarevich and her awesome students were recognized at tonight’s school board meeting for their achievements in Learning Ally’s reading competition. Their division of the contest had 332 schools entered in it. Selman Elementary placed 3rd in this national contest. We also had two students place in the top 10 individual students in the nation. Lainey Siska placed 5th and Antonio Cardenas placed 6th. We are extremely proud of Mrs. Magjarevich and all of these students!

post_text: TIGER PRIDE PROPS from Transportation: We had a parent say, "I just wanted to compliment the afternoon noon bus. I believe the number was 52. It goes through Ward Bend. post_text: TIGER PRIDE PROPS from SES: A parent emailed us to share, "Hi! I wanted to nominate Mrs. Gates for Tiger Pride Props! 👏🏼 Mrs. Gates is amazing in so many ways! Our oldest went to Kinder this year and as nervous as we were to be sending her off, we were at peace in so many different ways when we met Mrs. Gates. She has a loving presence and is so easy to communicate with. She has exceeded all of our expectations. And not to mention, our daughter is THRIVING. Mrs. Gates has proven that she is exactly where she needs to be. She is teaching all of our kids to the highest standard and is giving them all the skills they need to succeed. post_text:
The Texas Early Learning Council (TELC) is conducting a statewide survey to better understand the needs and challenges of those accessing, providing, and supporting early childhood programs and services in Texas.

The survey is open from Monday, March 25, 2019 to Friday, April 5, 2019 and should take no more than 20 minutes to complete. Questions intended
for families and early childhood program and service providers are available in both English and Spanish.

Who should take the survey?

- Families
- Staff of early childhood programs and services (childcare, Head Start, public prekindergarten, ECI, and home visiting)
- Staff of early childhood organizations (membership organizations, advocacy organizations, workforce boards, ESCs, etc.)
- Community organizations/partners (businesses, health service providers, local governments, religious organizations, etc.)

Please help us ensure the survey reaches as many Texans as possible by forwarding the survey to your family, friends, and colleagues.

https://tea.co1.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_cUeyDqwqLh2u8V7
